how naive were you as a child what are some funny incidents well i believed in santa clause and the easter bunny for a while i believed that others had my best interest at heart discovered that people have mostly their own interest at heart and i don't believe in organized religion now i do have a funny story about one of my sons though he was about years old and swimming in the local pool he was trying to get another kid to play with him and the kid thought that my son was too young to play and the older boy said you don't even know what a period is he was talking about women my son said i do too it is the dot at the end of a sentence i still laugh at the innocence and naivety of my little boys response at the time i was kind of proud of his response oh i do remember a story for you i had older siblings i was the youngest of five my mother had gone on some sort of errand and my older brothers got my sister and i to do the chores by telling us that we could ask the little man hidden in the wall of their bedroom for anything we wanted when we were done i imagined asking the little man for some desirable things while my sister and i finished the cleaning and of course there was no little man in the wall of their bedroom i was pretty upset lol Joke Shaggy dog story About a Boy Milton H. Erickson EastEnders Silent Night, Deadly Night Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Care Bears SpongeBob SquarePants Friends W.I.T.C.H. God Emperor of Dune Humphrey Bogart Social rule AFI 100 Years series One Tree Hill (TV series) Cliff Richard Dancing at Lughnasa Sin City Theory of conduct Knots Landing Baby Blues Fancy Crane Prince Edmund (Blackadder) Rich Mullins Pitaten The Catcher in the Rye Scouting Survivor (novel) Hilary Duff Marilyn Monroe Pip (South Park episode) Final Fantasy: Unlimited George Burns The Brothers Karamazov El Chavo del Ocho Billy the Kid Trailer Park Boys Pure Pwnage George Costanza Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Cigarette Smoking Man Pitcairn sexual assa